Minucius Felix is to help to remedy the abuse we refer to, by focusing attention once more on this gem of Christian literature. Minucius was probably the first of the Latin apologists of Christianity, and a study of his work is a most fitting introduction to the Latin Christian classics. While continental scholars have been busfly engaged in the elucidation of this author no English edition has appeared since the middle of the nineteenth century. The work of Holden will always command the respect of scholars, but scholarship has advanced since his day, and the very difficulty of procuring a copy of his work is sufficient apology for an independent edition.
